<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="1011" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1011">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/237.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-28T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 28, 1912—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 21, 10 p.m. The President on March 26 authorized by formal
                            order to the Treasury Department exceptions granting permission for the
                            exportation of the shipments, mentioned in your said telegram, to the
                            consignee in Mexico designated by the Mexican Embassy.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>